Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Item 2.02.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Results of Operations and Financial Condition.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom:12pt;margin-top:12pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt"><span style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">On February&#160;5, 2026, i3 Verticals, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) issued a press release announcing the results of its operations for the three months ended December 31, 2025. A copy of the press release is furnished as Exhibit 99.1 hereto and is hereby incorporated by reference into this Item 2.02.</span></div><div style="margin-top:12pt;text-align:justify"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Item 7.01.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Regulation FD Disclosure.</span></div><div style="text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt"><span><br/></span></div><div style="text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt"><span style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The Company has also prepared a supplemental presentation (the &#8220;Supplemental Presentation&#8221;) providing certain supplemental financial information for the three months ended December 31, 2025. A copy of the Supplemental Presentation is furnished as Exhibit 99.2 hereto and is hereby incorporated by reference into this Item 7.01. A copy of the Supplemental Presentation is also available on the Investors section of the Company&#8217;s website, www.i3verticals.com.</span></div><div style="text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt"><span><br/></span></div><div style="margin-bottom:12pt;text-align:justify"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Item 8.01.</span><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:12pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">             </span><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Other Events.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom:12pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:36pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">On February 5, 2026, the Company&#8217;s Board of Directors approved a new share repurchase program for the Company&#8217;s Class A common stock, under which the Company may repurchase up to $60 million of outstanding shares of Class A common stock (exclusive of fees, commissions or other expenses related to such repurchases). This new share purchase program replaces the Company&#8217;s prior share repurchase program under which the maximum dollar amount under the authorization has been expended.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom:12pt;text-indent:36pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">This share rep</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">urchase program will terminate on the earlier of February 4, 2027, or when the maximum dollar amount under the authorization has been expended. Pursuant to this authorization, repurchases may be made from time to time in the open market, through privately negotiated transactions, or otherwise, including under Rule 10b5-1 plans. In addition, any repurchases under this share repurchase program will be subject to prevailing market conditions, liquidity and cash flow considerations, applicable securities laws requirements (including under Rule 10b-18 and Rule 10b5-1 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as applicable), compliance with contractual restrictions under the Company&#8217;s credit facility, and other factors. This share repurchase program does not require the Company to acquire any particular amount of shares of Class A common stock, and may be extended, modified, suspended or discontinued at any time at the Company&#8217;s discretion.</span></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Item 9.01. operations</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:6.5pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.5pt;vertical-align:baseline">1,5</font><font respectively, representing a period-to-period growth rate of 8.4%.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;padding-left:21.6pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:14.5pt">Effective January&#160;1, 2026, the Company acquired a driver and motor vehicle insurance verification software company for $60.0 million in cash consideration, and an additional amount of cash contingent consideration in an amount not to exceed $20.0 million based on the performance of the acquired business for a period following the closing. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Greg Daily, Chairman and CEO of i3 Verticals, commented, &#34;We are pleased to report our first quarter of fiscal 2026 results, which were in line with our expectations and market guidance. While total revenue grew modestly at 1% year over year, recurring revenue increased by more than 8%, reflecting our long-term growth strategy. SaaS growth in the first quarter rose to 24%.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#34;I am very excited to announce our latest acquisition, effective January 1, 2026, which is a perfect fit within our transportation market. We self-sourced this transaction, and our deep relationships within the market made it possible. We believe the product has a unique competitive advantage, and the company has never lost a customer. The team brings an incredible track record, and it has been a pleasure welcoming them to i3. We are excited to do great things together!</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#34;While we&#8217;re pleased with our start to the fiscal year, we look forward to sharing more as the year progresses.&#34;</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:center"><font style="margin-bottom:6pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="height:54pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="-sec-extract:summary;text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">-MORE-</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:54pt;width:100%"><div style="-sec-extract:summary"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">IIIV Reports First Quarter 2026 Financial Results</font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Page 2</font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">February&#160;5, 2026</font></div></div><div style="padding-left:36pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">1.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">As a result of the sale of the Company&#8217;s merchant services business (the &#34;Merchant Services Business&#34;), which was completed on September 20, 2024, and the sale of the Company's Healthcare revenue cycle management business (&#34;Healthcare RCM Business&#34;), which was completed on May 5, 2025, the historical results of the Merchant Services Business and the Healthcare RCM Business have been reflected in discontinued operations in the consolidated statement of operations included in this earnings release, and continuing operations reflect the Company's remaining operations after giving effect to such classifications. Prior period results have been recast to reflect this presentation.</font></div><div style="padding-left:36pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">2.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Represents a non-GAAP financial measure. For additional information regarding non-GAAP financial measures (including reconciliation information), see the attached schedules to this release.</font></div><div style="padding-left:36pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">3.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Diluted net income (loss) per share attributable to Class A common stock from continuing operations and adjusted diluted earnings per share from continuing operations both exclude discontinued operations of the Merchant Services Business and the Healthcare RCM Business but include the consolidated cash interest expense. </font></div><div style="padding-left:36pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">4.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Corporate income tax expense is based on non-GAAP adjusted income before taxes from continuing operations and is calculated using a tax rate of 25.0% for both the three months ended December 31, 2025 and 2024, based on the estimated long-term effective tax rate, considering blended federal and state tax rates.</font></div><div style="padding-left:36pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">5.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Annualized Recurring Revenue (ARR) is the annualized revenue derived from recurring sources where the Company has an ongoing contract with its customers. The Company believes revenue from recurring sources is a strategic priority. ARR is comprised of software-as-a-service (&#8220;SaaS&#8221;) arrangements, transaction-based software-revenue, software maintenance, recurring software-based services, payments revenue and other recurring revenue sources within the quarter. The sum of these revenue categories is multiplied by four to calculate ARR. ARR excludes revenue that is not recurring or is one-time in nature. The Company's management believes this metric provides useful information to investors by providing visibility regarding the ongoing revenue potential of the Company's business model and providing a clearer picture of its sustainable revenue base. Further, the Company's management uses ARR as a metric because it helps to assess the health and trajectory of the Company's business. The Company's management believes that focusing on ARR can orient the Company's sales and operations management towards long-term, reliable revenue growth. This focus on recurring revenue is particularly relevant for businesses operating under a subscription model, where customer retention and contract renewals play a significant role in long-term financial performance. ARR does not have a standardized definition and is therefore unlikely to be comparable to similarly titled measures presented by other companies. It should be reviewed independently of revenue, and it is not a forecast. Additionally, ARR does not take into account seasonality. The active contracts at the end of a reporting period used in calculating ARR may or may not be extended or renewed by the Company's customers. </font></div><div style="height:54pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="-sec-extract:summary;text-align:center"><font guidance, excluding the impact of future acquisitions and transaction-related costs. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font long-term effective tax rate, considering blended federal and state tax rates. </font></div><div><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">With respect to the &#8220;2026 Outlook&#8221; above, reconciliations of adjusted EBITDA from continuing operations and adjusted diluted earnings per share from continuing operations guidance to the closest corresponding GAAP measure on a forward-looking basis are not available without unreasonable efforts. This inability results from the inherent difficulty in forecasting generally and quantifying certain projected amounts that are necessary for such reconciliations. In particular, sufficient information is not available to calculate certain adjustments required for such reconciliations, including changes in the fair value of contingent consideration, income tax expense of i3 Verticals, Inc. and equity-based compensation expense. The Company expects these adjustments may have a potentially significant impact on future GAAP financial results.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Conference Call</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The Company will host a conference call on Friday, February&#160;6, 2026, at 8&#58;30 a.m. EDT, to discuss financial results and operations. To listen to the call live via telephone, participants should dial (844)&#160;887-9399 approximately 10&#160;minutes prior to the start of the call. A telephonic replay will be available from 11&#58;30 a.m. EDT on February&#160;6, 2026, through February&#160;13, 2026, by dialing (855) 669-9658 and entering Confirmation Code 6769466.  </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">To listen to the call live via webcast, participants should visit the &#8220;Investors&#8221; section of the Company&#8217;s website, www.i3verticals.com, and go to the &#8220;Events&#8221; page approximately 10 minutes prior to the start of the call. The online replay will be available on this page of the Company&#8217;s website beginning shortly after the conclusion of the call and will remain available for 30 days. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Non-GAAP Measures</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">This press release contains information prepared in conformity with GAAP as well as non-GAAP information. It is management&#8217;s intent to provide non-GAAP financial information to enhance understanding of the Company's consolidated financial information as prepared in accordance with GAAP. This non-GAAP information should be considered by the reader in addition to, but not instead of, the financial statements prepared in accordance with GAAP. Each non-GAAP financial measure and the most directly comparable GAAP financial measure are presented for historical periods so as not to imply that more emphasis should be placed on the non-GAAP measure. The non-GAAP financial information presented may be determined or calculated differently by other companies.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Additional information about non-GAAP financial measures, and a reconciliation of those measures to the most directly comparable GAAP measures, is included in the financial schedules of this release.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">About i3 Verticals</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The Company provides mission-critical enterprise software solutions to public sector entities. These comprehensive cloud-native solutions address a broad range of government functions, including courts and public safety, public administration, utilities, transportation and schools. The Company&#8217;s mission is to enable state and local governments and related agencies to perform their functions and serve their constituents as effectively and efficiently as possible. With thousands of software installations across all 50 states and Canada, i3 Verticals is a leader in the public sector vertical. More information about the Company can be found at www.i3verticals.com. </font></div><div style="height:54pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">-MORE-</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:54pt;width:100%"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">IIIV Reports First Quarter Fiscal Year 2026 Financial Results</font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Page 4</font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">February&#160;5, 2026</font></div></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Forward-Looking Statements</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">This release contains forward-looking statements that are subject to risks and uncertainties. style="background-color:#cceeff;padding:2px 1pt 2px 0;text-align:right;vertical-align:bottom"></td></tr></table></div><div style="margin-bottom:2pt"><font><br></font></div><div id="i3d3254bed4de454b9782a108ea85f679_25"></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Reconciliation of GAAP to Non-GAAP Financial Measures</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The Company discloses the following non-GAAP financial measures in this earnings release&#58;</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:14.5pt">Adjusted Income Before Taxes from Continuing Operations. </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Adjusted income before taxes from continuing operations equals net income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to i3 Verticals Inc., adjusted to add back net income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to non-controlling interest and to exclude certain items on a pre-tax basis which the Company believes may not fully reflect our underlying operating performance. The Company believes that this non-GAAP measure provides useful information to investors in understanding and evaluating the Company&#8217;s results of continuing operations and ongoing operational performance on a pre-tax basis.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:14.5pt">Adjusted Net Income from Continuing Operations and Adjusted Diluted Earnings per Share from Continuing Operations. </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Adjusted net income from continuing operations equals adjusted income before taxes from continuing operations as described above, adjusted to give effect to an effective tax rate of 25%, which reflects our estimated long-term effective tax rate, considering blended federal and state tax rates. Adjusted diluted earnings per share from continuing operations equals adjusted net income from continuing operations divided by our adjusted weighted average shares of adjusted diluted Class A common stock outstanding. The Company believes that these non-GAAP measures provide useful information to investors in understanding and evaluating the Company&#8217;s results of continuing operations and ongoing operational performance on a post-tax basis after giving effect to this assumed tax rate. Adjusted Diluted Earnings per Share from Continuing Operations has also been utilized as a metric in connection with performance-based equity awards previously granted by the Company to executives.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:14.5pt">Adjusted EBITDA from Continuing Operations and Adjusted EBITDA Margin from Continuing Operations. </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Adjusted EBITDA from continuing operations equals net income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to i3 Verticals Inc., before interest, income taxes, depreciation and amortization, adjusted to add back net income (loss) from continuing operations attributable to non-controlling interest, and to exclude certain items which the Company believes do not fully reflect our underlying operating performance. Adjusted EBITDA margin represents adjusted EBITDA as a percentage of revenue. The Company believes that these non-GAAP measures provide useful information to investors in understanding and evaluating the Company&#8217;s results of continuing operations and ongoing operational performance. In addition, Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin have been metrics utilized in connection with the Company&#8217;s short-term annual cash incentive program for executive management.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The Company believes that the disclosure of these non-GAAP financial measures provides investors with useful information in connection with assessing the Company's financial results as described above. In addition, these non-GAAP financial measures are utilized by management to assess the Company's financial results, evaluate the Company's business, manage budgets, allocate resources, and make operational decisions. The Company believes that disclosure of these non-GAAP financial measures provides investors with additional information to help them better understand our financial results just as management utilizes these non-GAAP financial measures as described above. Although these non-GAAP financial measures assist in measuring the Company's financial results and assessing its financial performance, they are not necessarily comparable to similarly titled measures of other companies due to potential inconsistencies in the method of calculation.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">See below for reconciliations of the non-GAAP financial measures presented in this release. </font></div><div style="height:54pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">-MORE-</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:72pt;width:100%"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">IIIV Reports First Quarter Fiscal Year 2026 Financial Results</font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Page 8</font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">February&#160;5, 2026</font></div></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">i3 Verticals, Inc. Reconciliation of GAAP Net Income (Loss) from Continuing Operations to </font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Non-GAAP Adjusted Net Income from Continuing Operations and </font></div><div solid #000;padding:2px 1pt 2px 0;text-align:right;vertical-align:bottom"></td></tr></table></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">________________</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">1.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Non-cash change in fair value of contingent consideration reflects the changes in management&#8217;s estimates of future cash consideration to be paid in connection with prior acquisitions from the amount estimated as of the later of the most recent balance sheet date forming the beginning of the income statement period or the original estimates made at the closing of the applicable acquisition.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">2.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Equity-based compensation expense related to stock options and restricted stock units issued under the Company's 2018 Equity Incentive Plan and 2020 Acquisition Equity Incentive Plan.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">3.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">M&#38;A-related activity is the net impact of professional service and related costs directly related to any merger, acquisition and disposition activity of the Company (&#34;M&#38;A-related expenses&#34;), which are recorded in selling, general and administrative in the condensed consolidated statements of operations, and revenue earned through post-sale non-recurring activities with divestitures (&#34;M&#38;A-related income&#34;), which are recorded in other income in the condensed consolidated statements of operations. i3 Verticals believes these activities are not reflective of the underlying operational performance of the Company. M&#38;A-related income for the three months ended December 31, 2025 and 2024, was $166, and $495 respectively. M&#38;A-related expenses for the three months ended December 31, 2025 and 2024, were $187 and $546, respectively.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">4.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Acquisition intangible amortization reflects amortization of intangible assets and software acquired through acquisitions of business or other purchases of intangible assets.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">5.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Non-cash interest expense reflects amortization of debt issuance costs and any write-offs of debt issuance costs.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">6.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Other taxes consist of franchise taxes, commercial activity taxes, reserves for ongoing tax audit matters, the employer portion of payroll taxes related to stock option exercises and other non-income-based taxes. Taxes related to salaries are not included. </font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">7.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Loss (gain) on disposal of property and equipment is related to the sale of buildings and automobiles purchased through acquisitions. </font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">8.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Represents a non-GAAP financial measure.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">9.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:11.34pt">Corporate income tax expense is based on non-GAAP adjusted income before taxes from continuing operations and is calculated using a tax rate of 25.0% for both the three months ended December 31, 2025 and 2024, based on the estimated long-term effective tax rate, considering blended federal and state tax rates.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">10.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:6.9pt">Cash interest income, net, represents all interest expense net of interest income recorded on the Company's statement of operations other than non-cash interest expense, which represents amortization of debt issuance costs and any write-offs of debt issuance costs.</font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">11.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:6.9pt">Depreciation and internally developed software amortization reflects depreciation on the Company's property, plant and equipment, net, and amortization expense on its internally developed capitalized software.</font></div><div style="height:54pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div Further, adjusted diluted earnings per share from continuing operations assumes that all Common Units in i3 Verticals, LLC and the associated non-voting Class B common stock were exchanged for Class A common stock at the beginning of the period on a one-for-one basis. </font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">4.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%;padding-left:11.34pt">Adjusted net income from continuing operations, a non-GAAP financial measure, assumes that all net income from continuing operations during the period is available to the holders of the Company's Class A common stock. </font></div><div style="padding-left:18pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">5.</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%;padding-left:11.34pt">Adjusted weighted average shares of adjusted diluted Class A common stock outstanding include 8,381,681 and 10,026,180 weighted average outstanding shares of Class B common stock (which can be converted into Class A common stock upon the exchange of the Class B common stock and the associated Common Units in i3 Verticals, LLC) and&#160;1,416,679 and 479,664 shares resulting from estimated stock option exercises and restricted stock units vesting as calculated by the treasury stock method for the three months ended December 31, 2025 and 2024, respectively.</font></div><div style="height:54pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">-END-</font></div></div></div></body></html>

<DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">3 1.) As&#9;a&#9;result&#9;of&#9;the&#9;sale&#9;of&#9;our&#9;merchant&#9;services&#9;business&#9;(the&#9;&quot;Merchant&#9;Services&#9;Business&quot;),&#9;which&#9;was&#9;completed&#9;on&#9;September&#9;20,&#9;2024,&#9;and&#9;the&#9;sale&#9;of&#9;our&#9; Healthcare&#9;revenue&#9;cycle&#9;management&#9;business&#9;(the&#9;&quot;Healthcare&#9;RCM&#9;Business&quot;),&#9;which&#9;was&#9;completed&#9;on&#9;May&#9;5,&#9;2025,&#9;the&#9;historical&#9;results&#9;of&#9;the&#9; Merchant&#9;Services&#9;Business&#9;and&#9;the&#9;Healthcare&#9;RCM&#9;Business&#9;have&#9;been&#9;reflected&#9;in&#9;discontinued&#9;operations&#9;in&#9;the&#9;consolidated&#9;statement&#9;of&#9;operations&#9; included&#9;in&#9;this&#9;supplemental&#9;information,&#9;and&#9;continuing&#9;operations&#9;reflect&#9;our&#9;remaining&#9;operations&#9;after&#9;giving&#9;effect&#9;to&#9;such&#9;classifications.&#9;Prior&#9;period&#9; results&#9;have&#9;been&#9;recast&#9;to&#9;reflect&#9;this&#9;presentation. 2.) SaaS&#9;revenue&#9;is&#9;earned&#9;when&#9;we&#9;provide,&#9;as&#9;a&#9;service&#9;to&#9;our&#9;customers&#9;over&#9;time,&#9;the&#9;right&#9;to&#9;access&#9;our&#9;software. 3.) Transaction-based&#9;software&#9;revenue&#9;is&#9;earned&#9;when&#9;we&#9;provide&#9;services&#9;through&#9;our&#9;software&#9;and&#9;charge&#9;a&#9;per-transaction&#9;fee.&#9;For&#9;example,&#9;when&#9;we&#9; provide&#9;electronic&#9;filing&#9;services&#9;for&#9;courts&#9;and&#9;charge&#9;fees&#9;per&#9;filing,&#9;or&#9;when&#9;we&#9;stand-ready&#9;to&#9;process&#9;and&#9;bill&#9;utility&#9;customers&#9;and&#9;charge&#9;the&#9;utility&#9;a&#9;fee&#9; per&#9;bill&#9;electronically&#9;presented. 4.) Software&#9;maintenance&#9;revenue&#9;is&#9;earned&#9;when,&#9;following&#9;the&#9;implementation&#9;of&#9;our&#9;software&#9;systems,&#9;we&#9;provide&#9;ongoing&#9;software&#9;support&#9;services&#9;to&#9; assist&#9;our&#9;customers&#9;in&#9;operating&#9;the&#9;systems&#9;and&#9;to&#9;periodically&#9;update&#9;the&#9;software. 5.) Recurring&#9;software&#9;services&#9;are&#9;earned&#9;when&#9;we&#9;provide&#9;long-term,&#9;usually&#9;evergreen,&#9;contracted&#9;services&#9;to&#9;our&#9;customers&#9;through&#9;our&#9;software.&#9;The&#9; services&#9;provided,&#9;such&#9;as&#9;automated&#9;collections&#9;management,&#9;are&#9;integrated&#9;into&#9;one&#9;of&#9;our&#9;software&#9;solutions. 6.) Professional&#9;services&#9;are&#9;earned&#9;when&#9;we&#9;provide&#9;customized&#9;services&#9;to&#9;our&#9;customers&#9;who&#9;utilize&#9;our&#9;software&#9;products.&#9;Many&#9;of&#9;our&#9;customers&#9;contract&#9; with&#9;us&#9;for&#9;installation,&#9;configuration,&#9;training,&#9;and&#9;data&#9;conversion&#9;projects,&#9;which&#9;do&#9;not&#9;necessarily&#9;recur,&#9;and&#9;as&#9;such&#9;are&#9;excluded&#9;from&#9;our&#9;calculation&#9;of&#9; ARR. 7.) Recurring&#9;other&#9;revenue&#9;primarily&#9;consists&#9;of&#9;recurring&#9;long-term&#9;contracts&#9;that&#9;are&#9;not&#9;specific&#9;to&#9;software,&#9;such&#9;as&#9;hardware&#9;maintenance&#9;plans&#9;or&#9;field&#9; service&#9;plans. 8.) Recurring&#9;revenue&#9;consists&#9;of&#9;software-as-a-service&#9;(&#8220;SaaS&#8221;)&#9;arrangements,&#9;transaction-based&#9;software-revenue,&#9;software&#9;maintenance&#9;revenue,&#9;recurring&#9; software-based&#9;services,&#9;payments&#9;revenue&#9;and&#9;other&#9;recurring&#9;revenue&#9;sources.&#9;This&#9;excludes&#9;contracts&#9;that&#9;are&#9;not&#9;recurring&#9;or&#9;are&#9;one-time&#9;in&#9;nature.&#9; 9.) Annualized&#9;Recurring&#9;Revenue&#9;(ARR)&#9;is&#9;the&#9;annualized&#9;revenue&#9;derived&#9;from&#9;recurring&#9;sources&#9;where&#9;the&#9;Company&#9;has&#9;an&#9;ongoing&#9;contract&#9;with&#9;our&#9; customers.&#9;We&#9;believe&#9;revenue&#9;from&#9;recurring&#9;sources&#9;is&#9;a&#9;strategic&#9;priority.&#9;ARR&#9;is&#9;comprised&#9;of&#9;software-as-a-service&#9;(&#8220;SaaS&#8221;)&#9;arrangements,&#9;transaction- based&#9;software-revenue,&#9;software&#9;maintenance,&#9;recurring&#9;software-based&#9;services,&#9;payments&#9;revenue&#9;and&#9;other&#9;recurring&#9;revenue&#9;sources&#9;within&#9;the&#9; quarter.&#9;The&#9;sum&#9;of&#9;these&#9;revenue&#9;categories&#9;is&#9;multiplied&#9;by&#9;four&#9;to&#9;calculate&#9;ARR.&#9;ARR&#9;excludes&#9;revenue&#9;that&#9;is&#9;not&#9;recurring&#9;or&#9;is&#9;one-time&#9;in&#9;nature.&#9;We&#9; believe&#9;this&#9;metric&#9;provides&#9;useful&#9;information&#9;to&#9;investors&#9;by&#9;providing&#9;visibility&#9;regarding&#9;the&#9;ongoing&#9;revenue&#9;potential&#9;of&#9;our&#9;business&#9;model&#9;and&#9; providing&#9;a&#9;clearer&#9;picture&#9;of&#9;our&#9;sustainable&#9;revenue&#9;base.&#9;Further,&#9;management&#9;uses&#9;ARR&#9;as&#9;a&#9;metric&#9;because&#9;it&#9;helps&#9;to&#9;assess&#9;the&#9;health&#9;and&#9;trajectory&#9;of&#9; our&#9;business.&#9;Our&#9;management&#9;believes&#9;that&#9;focusing&#9;on&#9;ARR&#9;can&#9;orient&#9;our&#9;sales&#9;and&#9;operations&#9;management&#9;towards&#9;long-term,&#9;reliable&#9;revenue&#9;growth.&#9; This&#9;focus&#9;on&#9;recurring&#9;revenue&#9;is&#9;particularly&#9;relevant&#9;for&#9;businesses&#9;operating&#9;under&#9;a&#9;subscription&#9;model,&#9;where&#9;customer&#9;retention&#9;and&#9;contract&#9;renewals&#9; play&#9;a&#9;significant&#9;role&#9;in&#9;long-term&#9;financial&#9;performance.&#9;ARR&#9;does&#9;not&#9;have&#9;a&#9;standardized&#9;definition&#9;and&#9;is&#9;therefore&#9;unlikely&#9;to&#9;be&#9;comparable&#9;to&#9;similarly&#9; titled&#9;measures&#9;presented&#9;by&#9;other&#9;companies.&#9;It&#9;should&#9;be&#9;reviewed&#9;independently&#9;of&#9;revenue,&#9;and&#9;it&#9;is&#9;not&#9;a&#9;forecast.&#9;Additionally,&#9;ARR&#9;does&#9;not&#9;take&#9;into&#9; account&#9;seasonality.&#9;The&#9;active&#9;contracts&#9;at&#9;the&#9;end&#9;of&#9;a&#9;reporting&#9;period&#9;used&#9;in&#9;calculating&#9;ARR&#9;may&#9;or&#9;may&#9;not&#9;be&#9;extended&#9;or&#9;renewed&#9;by&#9;our&#9;customers.&#9; <DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">5 Quarterly Performance from Continuing  Operations 1.) Recurring&#9;cash&#9;other&#9;costs&#9;of&#9;services&#9;represents&#9;recurring&#9;operating&#9;costs&#9;directly&#9;related&#9;to&#9;our&#9;revenue&#9;generating&#9;activities&#9;except&#9;the&#9;stock&#9;compensation&#9;portion&#9;of&#9;personnel&#9;costs&#9; included&#9;within&#9;other&#9;costs&#9;of&#9;services. 2.) Recurring&#9;cash&#9;SG&amp;A&#9;expenses&#9;represents&#9;recurring&#9;operating&#9;costs&#9;such&#9;as&#9;certain&#9;people&#9;costs&#9;(for&#9;individuals&#9;not&#9;within&#9;other&#9;cost&#9;of&#9;services),&#9;technology,&#9;facilities,&#9;sales&#9;and&#9;marketing. 3.) Adjusted&#9;EBITDA&#9;margin&#9;represents&#9;adjusted&#9;EBITDA&#9;as&#9;a&#9;percentage&#9;of&#9;revenue.&#9;Adjusted&#9;EBITDA&#9;and&#9;Adjusted&#9;EBITDA&#9;margin&#9;are&#9;non-GAAP&#9;financial&#9;measures.&#9;For&#9;additional&#9;information&#9; regarding&#9;these&#9;non-GAAP&#9;financial&#9;measures,&#9;including&#9;reconciliations&#9;of&#9;Adjusted&#9;EBITDA&#9;to&#9;the&#9;most&#9;comparable&#9;GAAP&#9;measure.&#9;Refer&#9;to&#9;the&#9;following&#9;slides&#9;for&#9;the&#9;reconciliations&#9;of&#9; non-GAAP&#9;financial&#9;measures. ($&#9;in&#9;thousands) Three&#9;Months&#9;Ended December&#9;31,&#9; 2025 September&#9;30,&#9; 2025 June&#9;30,&#9;2025 March&#9;31,&#9;2025 December&#9;31,&#9; 2024 Revenue&#9;from&#9;continuing&#9;operations $&#9; 52,671&#9; $&#9; 54,901&#9; $&#9; 51,901&#9; $&#9; 54,135&#9; $&#9; 52,221&#9; Recurring&#9;cash&#9;other&#9;costs&#9;of&#9;services(1) &#9; 17,345&#9; &#9; 17,483&#9; &#9; 16,547&#9; &#9; 16,403&#9; &#9; 15,414&#9; Recurring&#9;cash&#9;SG&amp;A&#9;expenses(2) &#9; 16,875&#9; &#9; 18,811&#9; &#9; 18,117&#9; &#9; 17,399&#9; &#9; 17,261&#9; Corporate&#9;expenses &#9; 4,836&#9; &#9; 4,208&#9; &#9; 4,513&#9; &#9; 4,492&#9; &#9; 4,975&#9; Adjusted&#9;EBITDA&#9;from&#9;continuing&#9;operations(3) $&#9; 13,615&#9; $&#9; 14,399&#9; $&#9; 12,724&#9; $&#9; 15,841&#9; $&#9; 14,571&#9; Adjusted&#9;EBITDA&#9;margin&#9;from&#9;continuing&#9;operations(3) &#9;26&#9;% &#9;26&#9;% &#9;25&#9;% &#9;29&#9;% &#9;28&#9;% Period&#9;over&#9;period&#9;growth&#9;rates Y/Y Revenue&#9;from&#9;continuing&#9;operations 1% Recurring&#9;cash&#9;other&#9;costs&#9;of&#9;services(1) 13% Recurring&#9;cash&#9;SG&amp;A&#9;expenses(2) (2)% Corporate&#9;expenses (3)% Adjusted&#9;EBITDA&#9;from&#9;continuing&#9;operations(3) (7)% </FONT></DIV>

As&#9;a&#9;result&#9;of&#9;the&#9;sale&#9;of&#9;our&#9;merchant&#9;services&#9;business&#9;(the&#9;&quot;Merchant&#9;Services&#9;Business&quot;),&#9;which&#9;was&#9;completed&#9;on&#9;September&#9;20,&#9;2024,&#9;and&#9;the&#9;sale&#9;of&#9;our&#9;Healthcare&#9; revenue&#9;cycle&#9;management&#9;business&#9;(the&#9;&quot;Healthcare&#9;RCM&#9;Business&quot;),&#9;which&#9;was&#9;completed&#9;on&#9;May&#9;5,&#9;2025,&#9;the&#9;historical&#9;results&#9;of&#9;the&#9;Merchant&#9;Services&#9;Business&#9;and&#9;the&#9; Healthcare&#9;RCM&#9;Business&#9;have&#9;been&#9;reflected&#9;in&#9;discontinued&#9;operations&#9;in&#9;the&#9;consolidated&#9;statement&#9;of&#9;operations&#9;included&#9;in&#9;this&#9;supplemental&#9;information,&#9;and&#9;continuing&#9; operations&#9;reflect&#9;our&#9;remaining&#9;operations&#9;after&#9;giving&#9;effect&#9;to&#9;such&#9;classifications.&#9;Prior&#9;period&#9;results&#9;have&#9;been&#9;recast&#9;to&#9;reflect&#9;this&#9;presentation. 2.) Non-cash&#9;change&#9;in&#9;fair&#9;value&#9;of&#9;contingent&#9;consideration&#9;reflects&#9;the&#9;changes&#9;in&#9;management&#8217;s&#9;estimates&#9;of&#9;future&#9;cash&#9;consideration&#9;to&#9;be&#9;paid&#9;in&#9;connection&#9;with&#9;prior&#9; acquisitions&#9;from&#9;the&#9;amount&#9;estimated&#9;as&#9;of&#9;the&#9;later&#9;of&#9;the&#9;most&#9;recent&#9;balance&#9;sheet&#9;date&#9;forming&#9;the&#9;beginning&#9;of&#9;the&#9;income&#9;statement&#9;period&#9;or&#9;the&#9;original&#9;estimates&#9; made&#9;at&#9;the&#9;closing&#9;of&#9;the&#9;applicable&#9;acquisition. 3.) Equity-based&#9;compensation&#9;expense&#9;related&#9;to&#9;stock&#9;options&#9;and&#9;restricted&#9;stock&#9;units&#9;issued&#9;under&#9;the&#9;Company's&#9;2018&#9;Equity&#9;Incentive&#9;Plan&#9;and&#9;2020&#9;Acquisition&#9;Equity&#9; Incentive&#9;Plan. 4.) M&amp;A-related&#9;activity&#9;is&#9;the&#9;net&#9;impact&#9;of&#9;professional&#9;service&#9;and&#9;related&#9;costs&#9;directly&#9;related&#9;to&#9;any&#9;merger,&#9;acquisition&#9;and&#9;disposition&#9;activity&#9;of&#9;the&#9;Company&#9;(&quot;M&amp;A- related&#9;expenses&quot;),&#9;which&#9;are&#9;recorded&#9;in&#9;selling,&#9;general&#9;and&#9;administrative&#9;in&#9;the&#9;condensed&#9;consolidated&#9;statements&#9;of&#9;operations,&#9;and&#9;revenue&#9;earned&#9;through&#9;post-sale&#9; non-recurring&#9;activities&#9;with&#9;divestitures&#9;(&quot;M&amp;A-related&#9;income&quot;),&#9;which&#9;are&#9;recorded&#9;in&#9;other&#9;income&#9;in&#9;the&#9;condensed&#9;consolidated&#9;statements&#9;of&#9;operations.&#9;i3&#9;Verticals&#9; believes&#9;these&#9;activities&#9;are&#9;not&#9;reflective&#9;of&#9;the&#9;underlying&#9;operational&#9;performance&#9;of&#9;the&#9;Company.&#9;M&amp;A-related&#9;income&#9;was&#9;$166,&#9;$1,448,&#9;$4,237,&#9;$461,&#9;and&#9;$495&#9;for&#9;the&#9; three&#9;months&#9;ending&#9;December&#9;31,&#9;2025;&#9;September&#9;30,&#9;2025;&#9;June&#9;30,&#9;2025;&#9;March&#9;31,&#9;2025;&#9;and&#9;December&#9;31,&#9;2024,&#9;respectively.&#9;M&amp;A-related&#9;expenses&#9;were&#9;$187,&#9; $1,303,&#9;$5,373,&#9;$570,&#9;and&#9;$546&#9;for&#9;the&#9;three&#9;months&#9;ending&#9;December&#9;31,&#9;2025;&#9;September&#9;30,&#9;2025;&#9;June&#9;30,&#9;2025;&#9;March&#9;31,&#9;2025;&#9;and&#9;December&#9;31,&#9;2024,&#9;respectively.&#9; 5.) Acquisition&#9;intangible&#9;amortization&#9;reflects&#9;amortization&#9;of&#9;intangible&#9;assets&#9;and&#9;software&#9;acquired&#9;through&#9;acquisitions&#9;of&#9;business&#9;or&#9;other&#9;purchases&#9;of&#9;intangible&#9;assets. 6.) the&#9;treasury&#9;stock&#9;method. &#8226; For&#9;the&#9;three&#9;months&#9;ended&#9;September&#9;30,&#9;2025,&#9;adjusted&#9;weighted&#9;average&#9;shares&#9;of&#9;adjusted&#9;diluted&#9;Class&#9;A&#9;common&#9;stock&#9;outstanding&#9;include&#9;8,388,470&#9; weighted&#9;average&#9;outstanding&#9;shares&#9;of&#9;Class&#9;B&#9;common&#9;stock&#9;(which&#9;can&#9;be&#9;converted&#9;into&#9;Class&#9;A&#9;common&#9;stock&#9;upon&#9;the&#9;exchange&#9;of&#9;the&#9;Class&#9;B&#9;common&#9;stock&#9; and&#9;the&#9;associated&#9;Common&#9;Units&#9;in&#9;i3&#9;Verticals,&#9;LLC)&#9;and&#9;1,911,108&#9;shares&#9;resulting&#9;from&#9;estimated&#9;stock&#9;option&#9;exercises&#9;and&#9;restricted&#9;stock&#9;units&#9;vesting&#9;as&#9; calculated&#9;by&#9;the&#9;treasury&#9;stock&#9;method. &#8226; For&#9;the&#9;three&#9;months&#9;ended&#9;June&#9;30,&#9;2025,&#9;adjusted&#9;weighted&#9;average&#9;shares&#9;of&#9;adjusted&#9;diluted&#9;Class&#9;A&#9;common&#9;stock&#9;outstanding&#9;include&#9;8,637,499&#9;weighted&#9; average&#9;outstanding&#9;shares&#9;of&#9;Class&#9;B&#9;common&#9;stock&#9;(which&#9;can&#9;be&#9;converted&#9;into&#9;Class&#9;A&#9;common&#9;stock&#9;upon&#9;the&#9;exchange&#9;of&#9;the&#9;Class&#9;B&#9;common&#9;stock&#9;and&#9;the&#9; associated&#9;Common&#9;Units&#9;in&#9;i3&#9;Verticals,&#9;LLC)&#9;and&#9;952,796&#9;shares&#9;resulting&#9;from&#9;estimated&#9;stock&#9;option&#9;exercises&#9;and&#9;restricted&#9;stock&#9;units&#9;vesting&#9;as&#9;calculated&#9;by&#9; // Edgar(tm) Renderer was created by staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Data and content created by government employees within the scope of their employment are not subject to domestic copyright protection. 17 U.S.C. 105.
var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}
